d-member-list">    <div class="row ">	    <div class="col-md-2 text-center">    	    <img src="./Board_files/photo2.gif" class="img-circle">	    </div>        <div class="col-md-10">            <h4 class="u-title">Katherine Monroe<br>Vice-President</h4>            <div class="u-desc"><p>Katherine Monroe joined the NCCAA in 2013, serving as Secretary/Treasurer from 2013-2018 and as Vice Chair since 2019. She graduated from Emory's Master of Medical Science Program in Anesthesiology in 2002 and completed her Ph.D. in Higher Education Leadership at Mercer University in 2014.			<br><br>			Katie was a member of the Accreditation Review Committee for Anesthesiologist Assistants (ARC-AA) from 2004-2010, served as Vice-Chair from 2008-2010, and continues to participate as a site visitor for the ARC-AA. She fulfilled a term on the AAAA Board of Directors from 2013-2013, and she currently serves on the Georgia Academy of Anesthesiologist Assistants Board of Directors.			<br><br>			Katie is the Academic Program Director of the Emory Anesthesiologist Assistant Program and practices clinically at Children’s Healthcare of Atlanta at Egleston.			</p></div>            </div>    </div><!--//row//--></div><div class=" board-member-list">    <div class="row ">	    <div class="col-md-2 text-center">    	    <img src="./Board_files/photo3.gif" class="img-circle">	    </div>        <div class="col-md-10">            <h4 class="u-title">Jana McAlister<br>Secretary/Treasurer</h4>            <div class="u-desc"><p> 			<br><br>			 			</p></div>            </div>    </div><!--//row//--></div><div class=" board-member-list">    <div class="row ">	    <div class="col-md-12 text-left" style="margin-bottom: 20px;">    	    <p>Board Members</p>	    </div>	    <div class="col-md-2 text-center">    	    <img src="./Board_files/photo4.gif" class="img-circle">	    </div>        <div class="col-md-10">            <h4 class="u-title">Sherry Adamic</h4>            <div class="u-desc"><p> <br><br>			 			</p></div>            </div>    </div><!--//row//--></div><div class=" board-member-list">    <div class="row ">	    <div class="col-md-2 text-center">    	    <img src="./Board_files/photo5.gif" class="img-circle">	    </div>        <div class="col-md-10">            <h4 class="u-title">Matthew Ciotti</h4>            <div class="u-desc"><p>Matthew Ciotti is a Certified Anesthesiologist Assistant who has been serving on the NCCAA Board of Directors since January, 2019. Matthew graduated from Case Western Reserve University’s MSA program in Cleveland, Ohio in 2008. He currently practices at The Christ Hospital in Cincinnati, Ohio serving as Chief Anesthetist.			<br><br>			In addition to serving the CAA community in a director’s (commissioner’s?) role with the NCCAA, Matthew has sat on the Commission’s Test Writing Committee since 2012. He is also currently a board member in the Ohio Academy of Anesthesiologist Assistants and previously held the position of President within that organization.<br><br>			Matthew currently resides in Cincinnati with his wife Kayla and two young children.  			</p></div>            </div>		    </div><!--//row//--></div><div class=" board-member-list">    <div class="row ">	    <div class="col-md-2 text-center">    	    <img src="./Board_files/photo6.gif" class="img-circle">	    </div>        <div class="col-md-10">            <h4 class="u-title">Lois Connolly</h4>            <div class="u-desc"><p>I am a Tenured Professor in the Department of Anesthesiology at the Medical College of Wisconsin. Over my career, I have served in many different leadership positions and have lead many strategic projects both through Froedtert Hospital and Medical College of Wisconsin. One such project is the Medical College of Wisconsin's Master of Science in Anesthesia (MSA), Anesthesiologist Assistant Program, for which I serve as Medical Director. The MSA program is the first allied health program at the Medical College of Wisconsin, launched in 2016 as the 11th Anesthesiologist Assistant Program in the USA and serves as a footprint for future allied health programs at MCW. Clinically, I am an academic neuroanesthesiologist and a liver transplant anesthesiologist. 			<br><br>			I am actively involved in teaching residents as well as MSA students within my subspecialty areas. I serve as Governor appointee to the Wisconsin Medical Examining Board, Council on Anesthesiologist Assistants as well as Commissioner on NCCAA. I serve as Alternate Director on the Board of Directors at the American Society of Anesthesiologists and chair ASA Committee on Quality Management and Departmental Administration.			</p></div>            </div>    </div><!--//row//--></div><div class=" board-member-list">    <div class="row ">	    <div class="col-md-2 text-center">    	    <img src="./Board_files/photo7.gif" class="img-circle">	    </div>        <div class="col-md-10">            <h4 class="u-title">Joe Mader</h4>            <div class="u-desc"><p>I graduated from the CWRU AA program in 1998 and was invited to join the NCCAA test writing committee a few years after. I have served on the NCCAA Board of Commissioners since 2013. I currently work in private practice in Springfield, OH.			<br><br>			</p></div>            </div>		    </div><!--//row//--></div><div class=" board-member-list">    <div class="row ">	    <div class="col-md-2 text-center">    	    <img src="./Board_files/photo8.gif" class="img-circle">	    </div>        <div class="col-md-10">            <h4 class="u-title">Paul McHorse</h4>            <div class="u-desc">			<p>			Paul McHorse joined the NCCAA Board in 2019. He is a 1999 graduate of the Emory Masters of Medical Science in Anesthesiology and Patient Monitoring Systems. Upon graduation, he became one of the first CAA’s in the state of Texas. Paul helped found the Texas Academy of Anesthesiologist Assistants and served as President until 2019. He also currently serves on the TXAAA Board of Directors. Paul currently practices clinically with Baylor Scott and White Health at their Round Rock campus.   <br><br>			</p></div>            </div>    </div><!--//row//--></div><div class=" board-member-list">    <div class="row ">	    <div class="col-md-2 text-center">    	    <img src="./Board_files/photo9.gif" class="img-circle">	    </div>        <div class="col-md-10">            <h4 class="u-title">Stacie Wong</h4>            <div class="u-desc"><p>Stacie Wong joined the NCCAA in 2013 and has been an active member of the NCCAA Test Committee since 2004. She received her bachelor’s degree from Harvard University and her medical degree from the Medical College of Georgia. Following residency training at the Medical College of Georgia, Stacie completed her fellowship at the University of Iowa. Stacie has served as the Medical Director of the South University Anesthesiologist Assistant Program since 2004. Her clinical work has taken her to multiple sites across the country as well as to Guatemala for mission work.  Since 2015 she has been a staff anesthesiologist at Meadows Regional Medical Center in Vidalia, Georgia where she also serves on multiple physician committees. 			<br><br>			 			</p></div>            </div>    </div><!--//row//--></div><div class=" board-member-list">    <div class="row ">	    <div class="col-md-12 text-left" style="margin-bottom: 20px;">    	    <p>CEO</p>	    </div>	    <div class="col-md-2 text-center">    	    <img src="./Board_files/photo10.gif" class="img-circle">	    </div>        <div class="col-md-10">            <h4 class="u-title">Soren Campbell</h4>            <div class="u-desc"><p> 			<br><br>			 			</p></div>            </div>    </div><!--//row//--></div>            </div>       